=== r1 ===

Release date: 1/02/2015
Initial release.


=== r2 ===

Release date: 6/03/2015
Major feature addition: Handovers
Other notable changes:
  - route parsing and next waypoint display
  - quick reference
  - save racks


=== r3 ===

Release date: 21/03/2015
Major feature addition: Background images
Other notable changes:
  - custom navigation data
  - configurable FGCom ports
  - save window state and geometry
  - separation rings


=== r4 ===

Release date: 21/05/2015
Major feature addition: Solo training mode
Other notable changes:
  - windsocks
  - FGCom server choice
  - route on strip display
  - strip colour for "!!vect"
  - instruction panel
  - saved RWY parameters
  - BG image example
  - speed info for a few ACFT types

Update r4b

Update r4c


=== r5 ===

Release date: 19/07/2015
Major feature addition: Path conflict detection
Other notable changes:
  - route drawing
  - SHIFT+click on navpoints for quick route editing
  - customisable colours
  - custom text aliases
  - warn of protocol-lost text messages
  - text labels in "DRAW" files
  - radar signal pick-up floor option
  - "kill ACFT" cheat

Update r5b:
  - check text alias replacements dialog


=== r6 ===

Release date: 16/08/2015
Major feature addition: Tower viewing
Other notable changes:
  - multiple weather stations
  - multiple radar screens
  - discarded strip recall cheat
  - spawn aircraft cheat
  - multi-view packet forwarding
  - ACFT type recognition and ICAO label on strips

Update r6b

Update r6c:
  - code optimisation
  - recognise airports, search and pick by name
  - show non-editable strip details
  - flight rules on strips
  - a few more options (and more saved)
  - small GUI changes, e.g. more compact radios
  - allow changing FG root directory


=== r7 ===

Release date: 21/09/2015
Major feature addition: Route viewer
Other notable changes:
  - text radio sender blacklist
  - chat completer: match anywhere in messages + popup
  - commercial callsigns generated in solo mode
  - easy access to Earth coordinates
  - strict ICAO designators option
  - notification on emergency code squawks
  - better FPL date filtering options

Update r7b:
  - configurable map and radar ranges
  - route presets by dep+dest airports
  - bg-img "point>radial,distance" spec
  - non-SX entries in ATC list (strip drops disabled)
  - "primary radar" option (no more an "OFF/STBY" cheat)
  - support for METAR "MPS" wind unit


=== r8 ===

Release date: 18/01/2016
Major feature addition: CTR mode
Other notable changes:
  - "!!route" warning
  - new "follow route" instruction and AI capability
  - tower icon in airport objects
  - packaged FGCom binaries upgrade to version 3.7

Update r8b:
  - draw additional airports
  - Lenny64 FPL management and session announcement use email+pwd

Update r8c:
  - alarm clocks (custom timers)
  - reload bg-img & route presets

Update r8d


=== r9 ===

Release date: 8/05/2016
Major feature addition: Tutorial sessions (connect teacher & student)
Other notable changes:
  - download OpenStreetMap images for radar background
  - holding instructions in solo sessions
  - wake turbulence category detail
  - lose contacts after invisible radar blip count (not timeout)


=== r10 ===

Release date: 10/07/2016
Major feature addition: Ground control (taxiways, parking, instructions...)
Other notable changes:
  - X-plane data update
  - individual aircraft freeze by teacher
  - randomise weather in solo sessions
  - wind affects AI aircraft
  - controllable strip auto-fill options
  - rack colours on tabs
  - sequence numbers on racks
  - custom airport spec vs. X-plane extract distinction
  - reload colour configuration file

Update r10b:
  - teacher keeps strips on handovers

Update r10c:
  - "navpoint~refpoint" syntax for point specs

Update r10d

Update r10e:
  - better final approach guides
  - configurable AMSL offset

Update r10f:
  - X-plane navaid & fix data update
  - WTC in radar tags

Update r10g:
  - pretty strips for all platforms
  - sector file data extracting script

Update r10h:
  - auto-remove strip assignments with instructions
  - sector file extraction script reads from SID/STAR/ARTCC sections


=== 0.9 ===

Version 0.9.1 release date: 26/09/2016
Major feature addition: Loose strip bays and column rack views
Other notable changes:
  - editable ACFT data base
  - open/close FPLs
  - airline livery configuration for AI traffic rendering
  - mode S radar identification
  - draw airport lines (X-plane "linear features")
  - WTC auto-fill button on detail sheets
  - manual control of saved radar pinned points and labels
  - preset text radio messages saved in separate file

Update 0.9.2:
  - position history trace instead of speed line
  - configurable course/hdg line fly time
  - FPL online updates reflected locally
  - +/- buttons in loose strip bays

Update 0.9.3


=== 1.0 ===

Version 1.0.1 release date: 6/12/2016
Major feature addition: runway boxes with automatic timers
Other notable changes:
  - GUI launcher & change location
  - relative wind direction in runway use selection dialog
  - more system & tower options from settings dialog box

Update 1.0.2:
  - avoid opposite runways in RWY use dialog
  - sync RWY label visibility with runway use selection


