=== 1.6 ===

Version 1.6.0 release date: 31/03/2019
Major feature addition: controller-pilot data link communication (CPDLC)
Other notable changes:
  - RDF in FlightGear sessions
  - AWY data and route suggestion
  - AD entry/exit point specification
  - extended teaching console (ACFT touch-and-go, visibility, clouds...)
  - radar tag line order option
  - VFR/IFR strip border indication
  - cheated radar contact tag border indication
  - AD drawing: TWY holding and centre lines, less TWY labelling clutter
  - last QDM in RDF status bar label
  - transition altitude sourced from apt.dat when present
  - per-model height offset for AI/teacher traffic

Update 1.6.1:
  - CPDLC "REQUEST" messages
  - RDF frequency selection in radio boxes

Update 1.6.2:
  - CPDLC status integration to strips
  - custom ATIS appendix template per AD location
  - text aliases $atis and $vis
  - RWY excursion option on teacher ACFT touch-down
  - free path for FGCom executable
  - type disambiguation in point specification strings

Update 1.6.3:
  - speed format and WTC position options in radar tags
  - rack sequence numbers on radar screen option
  - flag radar contact (manual colour highlight)
  - show ACFT cheat toggles menu option
  - X-plane 11 nav data format compatibility
  - grouped custom/editable data and settings into single directory
  - region disambiguation in point specification strings
  - nav data error log file
  - customisable Qt stylesheet for session window

Update 1.6.4

Update 1.6.5:
  - RWY separation timer reset
  - strip lower border toggle
  - radar tag WTC not shown option

